<td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%">
<p>Started a cleric awhile back up to 19 and looking to start doing LDON stuff. Mostly to now I have been grouping for fast exp, but now my role is starting to become important but having never played a cleric I have a few questions or need some tips.  <br />1. should i buff all members in group or just MA? <br />2. To conserve mana have you found healing or heal over time to work better? <br />3. Should i bother with nukes or save mana for heals. <br />4. Basically wondering some playing habits others have formed to help me become a better cleric. <br /> <br />Does anyone have a problem asking rangers and pallies to heal themselves between fights or do they need mana for pulling and buffing themselves.  <br /> <br />I have other characters but have never played one with a single roll like this before and any easy advice would be helpful thank you much. </p>
</td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td class="fs8"></td><td align="right" class="fs8" >6 replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table>
</td></tr><tr><td colspan="2"><table class="mform2"  border="0" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
