		   <span class="sm">Posted: Jan 17th  2004 at  5:33pm EDT<span class="notbold">| <span class="sm">IP: Logged</span> | <a class="sm" href="/db/classes.html?class=7;mid=107426688117461;num=6;page=1;post=1;replyto=1074375101524464514"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply..." height="11" width="17" /> Reply to this</a>    </span></span></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" class="mform2" ><span class="fs8"><span class="notbold">By: </span><a href="/db/poster.html?user=181670"><span class="">divinentia</span></a><b><span class=""></span></b><br /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><br />185 posts
		   <br /><span class="nobr"><span class="notbold">Score</span>: Default  </span><br />
<br/><a href="/db/classes.html?class=7;mid=107426688117461;page=1;howmany=50#1074375101524464514"><img alt="" title="Use this to create a link to this post" src="/shared/garrowrt.png" border="0" height="9" width="11" /> Link to this post</a>

<br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1" alt=""/></span></td>
<td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%">
<p>1) When I'm doing LDoN adventures, I usually buff everyone that askes for it. So, you might want to give everyone your best HP/AC buff, and if you have any regent HP buffs (symbols, aegolism line), you can go ahead and throw that one on as well.  <br /> <br />2) For the tanks, I use the regular heals. For anyone else that may be hurt by some trap or something, I use heals over time, or ask the SHM/DRU to heal. <br /> <br />3) You should NOT nuke. Most likely than not, you'll have someone else with you that can out-nuke you, and if you are nuking, you might go OOM faster, which leads to un-needed med times, and you might fail the adventure. <br /> <br />4) When doin an adventure, make sure you ALWAYS have root and divine aura ready. Sometimes, you're gonna hafta root adds when you have no ENC. I can't really say much else about number 4 - it's all about personal experience and finding you own strengths and weaknesses with the class you chose.</p>
